< PRIVACY POLICY >
Last updated: [22-05-2025]

1. Introduction
Welcome to TriviaTap, a mobile trivia app designed for entertainment and learning. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle your information when you use our app.

2. Information We Collect
TriviaTap does not collect or store any personal information from users.
However, we use third-party services, including Google AdMob, which may collect and process certain types of data automatically, such as:
- Device identifiers (e.g. Android Advertising ID)
- Usage data (e.g. ad clicks, impressions)
- Approximate location (based on IP address)
This information is used solely to support app functionality, display ads, and improve performance.

3. Third-Party Services
We use Google AdMob to serve ads within the app. AdMob may collect data to personalize ads or for analytics purposes. You can learn more about how Google handles your data here:
--  https://policies.google.com/privacy
Users can choose to disable personalized ads in their Google account or device settings.

4. Data Storage
TriviaTap does not transmit or store any user data on external servers. All preferences and settings are stored locally on the userâ€™s device.

5. Childrenâ€™s Privacy
TriviaTap is not directed at children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect any personal information from children.

6. User Controls
Users may:
- Limit data collection by disabling ad personalization
- Use app features without creating an account or sharing personal information

7. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be reflected in the "Last updated" date above.

